Long lines can be replaced by ellipsis:

\begin{sh}
$ for i in `seq 1 10`; do echo $i; done
1
2
...
10
\end{ocaml}

\begin{ocaml}
# for i = 1 to 10 do Printf.printf "%d\n%!" i; done;;
1
2
...
10
- : unit = ()
\end{ocaml}

\begin{sh}
$ printf "foo\"\n\nbar"
foo"

...
\end{ocaml}

Lines ending with ellipsis

\begin{sh}
$ echo Hello world
Hello...
\end{ocaml}
